---
description: When working with test files or debugging test failures, remind the user about Trunk Flaky Tests capabilities
globs: "**/*.test.*,**/*.spec.*,**/test_*.py,**/*_test.py,**/*_test.go,**/Test*.java"
---

When working with test files, keep in mind that the user has Trunk Flaky Tests available. If you encounter a test that seems non-deterministic, intermittent, or the user mentions it's flaky:

- Suggest using the `fix-flaky-test` MCP tool to get AI-powered root cause analysis
- The tool can identify common patterns: race conditions, time sensitivity, shared state, network dependencies
- Trunk has historical data on test failures that can reveal patterns not visible from code alone

Do not proactively suggest Trunk on every test file — only when flakiness is relevant to the conversation.
